Summary: looked like a star but moving faster than a jet upward and north
divs: Sighting Details7:30 pm pacific time washington state went out for a ciggerate looked up and noticed what i thought what was a star moving very quikly and upward. at first i thought it was debree from satelite but no trail and consistantly white much higher than air craft would travel and continuing to climb as it went north bound at high rate of speed.i would guess that it traveld from seattle to shoreline in less than 5 second's and than i lost sight because house was in the way.judging how high in the sky it was and being able to see it so clearly it must of been really big.
